Hiring an agent to sell your home is a big decision. And here’s the thing. It’s way more than finding someone who lives in your town. It’s about trust, comfort, and confidence. 

When looking for an agent, don’t overlook one or more of these red flags before making your final decision:

🚩 They have little to no online presence. 
🚩 They seem unfamiliar with your neighborhood.
🚩 When you meet face to face, they’re constantly checking their Apple watch, and you’re never quite sure if they’re listening.
🚩 It takes several attempts — on YOUR end — to reach them or get your questions answered.
🚩 Your gut tells you they’re just not it. 

Hiring the wrong agent to sell your home is like waking up on Christmas morning with coal in your stocking — ugh! So save this post for later, or tag someone you know who’s thinking about selling.

Invest in real estate!

Imagine how amazing it would feel to finally pull together a plan to invest in real estate. If this sounds like something that sparks joy for you, then imagine no more because I can make this a reality! Plus, there's no time like the present to get started!

Here's one of the easiest ways to start your investment journey:

Step 1: Buy a house, condo, or townhome in an up- and coming or in-demand neighborhood or school district. (PS - I can help!)

Step 2: Move in, and live life! As you do, get the home looking better than it did when you bought it by making small cosmetic changes.

Step 3: After a year or two, buy a new home, and rent out the first one. (But remember, rental income is taxed as ordinary income, so make sure to plan ahead for tax season!)

Step 4: Wash, rinse, and repeat!
By living in a house before renting it out, you can finance it as a residence, which will land you far better terms on a loan. 

Sound like a plan you're ready to execute? DM me, and let's get the pieces in place. It'll take a few years, but this is one of the safest ways to invest in real estate and see some great returns!

Building your dream home? 🏡✨Here are 10 amazing reasons to consider! From customization to energy efficiency, the possibilities are endless when you build from the ground up. 💪💡

Certainly! Here are some compelling reasons why you should consider building your own home:

1. Customization: Building allows you to design and customize every aspect of your home, ensuring it fits your unique preferences and needs.

2. Energy Efficiency: You can incorporate energy-efficient features and materials, saving on long-term utility costs and reducing your carbon footprint.

3. Quality Control: Building a home allows you to oversee the construction process, ensuring high-quality craftsmanship and materials.

4. Future-Proofing: You can incorporate technology and features that make your home more adaptable to future needs and trends.

5. Location Choice: You have more flexibility in choosing the perfect location for your new home, whether it's a quiet suburb or a bustling city center.

6. Financial Investment: Building can be a sound financial investment, as you often build equity faster compared to buying an existing home.

7. Warranty and Newness: New homes typically come with warranties on appliances and construction, giving you peace of mind.

8. Personal Satisfaction: The sense of accomplishment and pride in creating your dream home is unparalleled.

9. Energy Codes: You can comply with the latest energy codes and standards, resulting in a more comfortable and cost-effective living environment.

10. Unique Design: Building allows you to create a home that reflects your personal style and preferences, making it truly one-of-a-kind.

Remember that building a home is a significant undertaking, so it's essential to carefully consider your budget, timeline, and specific needs before starting the process.
